"### Sum of 5 learning trials for the RAVLT
Summary variables can be calculated and added to the ABCD data on DEAP. Here an example that calculates a simple sum of 5 learning trials from the Ray-Auditory Verbal Learning Task. We pull the raw values first:
```
var promises = use(["pea_ravlt_sd_trial_i_tc", "pea_ravlt_sd_trial_ii_tc", "pea_ravlt_sd_trial_iii_tc", "pea_ravlt_sd_trial_iv_tc", "pea_ravlt_sd_trial_v_tc"]);
```
This function calculates the sum of the 5 values if they all exist (not missing):
```
function calcRAVLTSum(a, b, c, d, e) {
    if (isNaN(a) || isNaN(b) || isNaN(c) || isNaN(d) || isNaN(e)) {
        return NaN;
    }
    return +a+b+c+d+e;
}
```

And here we call the function above for all the participants. The result is stored in the new variable <code>pea_ravlt_sum_trials</code>.
```
Promise.all(promises).then( function() {
  var data = new DataFrame(allMeasures);
  data = data.map(row => row.set("pea_ravlt_sum_trials", +calcRAVLTSum(row.get("pea_ravlt_sd_trial_i_tc"), row.get("pea_ravlt_sd_trial_ii_tc"), row.get("pea_ravlt_sd_trial_iii_tc"), row.get("pea_ravlt_sd_trial_iv_tc"), row.get("pea_ravlt_sd_trial_v_tc"))  ));
  update(data, 'pea_ravlt_sum_trials');
});
```
